     1	# Claude Finalizer — Spec Boundary Harness
     2	
     3	You receive a Codex validation report for a feature you (Claude) just produced.
     4	Your job is to triage every finding and apply the safe accepted ones, then write a triage report and a final report.
     5	
     6	You are still the **main author** of the artifacts; Codex is the **reviewer**. Do not blindly accept Codex findings; do not silently ignore critical ones either.
     7	
     8	---
     9	
    10	## Inputs
    11	
    12	- `reports/codex-validation-report.json` (canonical, schema-validated)
    13	- `reports/codex-validation-report.md` (human-readable mirror)
    14	- All 11 artifacts under `specs/<feature-id>/`
    15	- The original input directory
    16	- The repo-wide profile and rules
    17	
    18	---
    19	
    20	## Process
    21	
    22	1. Open `reports/codex-validation-report.json`. For each finding:
    23	   - **Accept** if: the finding is correct, the fix is local and safe (re-categorize a requirement, add a missing state, change a packet status from READY to BLOCKED, add a missing security warning, remove a stray server-only mention from a frontend packet, add `security: [{ bearerAuth: [] }]` to an auth-required endpoint, etc).
    24	   - **Reject** if: the finding is wrong (false positive), or accepting would violate a non-negotiable principle in `prompts/claude-analyzer.md`. Document the reason.
    25	   - **Needs human decision** if: the change is structural, ambiguous, or would require a product decision (e.g. "is Kakao login in scope or not?"). Do not auto-apply.
    26	2. For every accepted finding, apply the change to the relevant file under `specs/<feature-id>/`. Use the Edit tool. Keep the change minimal.
    27	3. For every rejected finding, **add a regression-style assertion** to `specs/<feature-id>/11-validation-summary.md` (a short bullet describing why the harness considers this acceptable).
    28	4. After applying all accepted changes, re-read the files and double-check the boundary rules from `prompts/claude-analyzer.md` still hold.
    29	
    30	---
    31	
    32	## Outputs
    33	
    34	Write **two files**:
    35	
    36	### `reports/codex-triage.md`
    37	
    38	```markdown
    39	# Codex Triage — <feature-id>
    40	
    41	Source: `reports/codex-validation-report.md` (generated <timestamp>)
    42	
    43	## Accepted findings (applied in this loop)
    44	
    45	| id | validator | severity | finding | action taken |
    46	|---|---|---|---|---|
    47	| ... | ... | ... | ... | ... |
    48	
    49	## Rejected findings
    50	
    51	| id | finding | reason |
    52	|---|---|---|
    53	| ... | ... | ... |
    54	
    55	## Needs human decision
    56	
    57	| id | finding | question |
    58	|---|---|---|
    59	| ... | ... | ... |
    60	
    61	## Notes
    62	
    63	(Anything important about how the triage was performed.)
    64	```
    65	
    66	### `specs/<feature-id>/11-validation-summary.md` (overwrite the placeholder)
    67	
    68	```markdown
    69	# Validation Summary — <title> (<feature-id>)
    70	
    71	Codex validator finished: <timestamp>
    72	Findings: <count> total — accepted=<n>, rejected=<n>, needs_human=<n>
    73	
    74	## Top findings
    75	
    76	- [<severity>] <validator>: <message>
    77	  - Decision: accepted | rejected | needs_human
